Lamb of god totally defied this .  Their genres (and this is 100% true ) were :  PURE. AMERICAN. METAL.   So badass .

snippet.textDisplay: Memento is the 2nd person singular active imperative of meminī, "to remember, to bear in mind", usually serving as a warning: "remember!" Mori is the present infinitive of the deponent verb morior, literally "to die". In other words, "remember death" or "remember that you will die".

snippet.textDisplay: I have this song on repeat everyday. I love Lamb of God. Love every album by them.  and will always be a huge fan. I love Randy's calm singing voice in the beginning and near the end. It gives me goosebumps everytime and his screams... Fucking amazing. The lyrics are so dark, but describe my life and story well. Willie and Mark kill it at those badass guitar riffs. John's bass is dead on, accurate, and can hear it really  good. Art Cruz will never be a Chris Atler, but he was the perfect replacement for the drummer of the band. I love Art's twist too the drums!!
snippet.textOriginal: I have this song on repeat everyday. I love Lamb of God. Love every album by them.  and will always be a huge fan. I love Randy's calm singing voice in the beginning and near the end. It gives me goosebumps everytime and his screams... Fucking amazing. The lyrics are so dark, but describe my life and story well. Willie and Mark kill it at those badass guitar riffs. John's bass is dead on, accurate, and can hear it really  good. Art Cruz will never be a Chris Atler, but he was the perfect replacement for the drummer of the band. I love Art's twist too the drums!!

snippet.textDisplay: Laughing at my own dumb ass, I started to give this a thumbs down until I realized I had watched the whole thing at 1.75 speed the first time. Duh, no wonder it sounded funny. I am sure hoping this Kung Flu B.S. has blown over by the end of July so I can see these guys again. Got the tickets as soon as they went on sale. Saw them on Slayer's Farewell tour and they stole the show. Why aren't these guys headlining yet?!! An old Metalhead would like to know.
